					<p>Sailors from novices through to capable club sailors are well 
					catered for at the club. Those want to learn can also join one of our
					 RYA recognised training courses.<br>
					 <br>
					 We run a full racing programme from March until Boxing Day.</p>
					
					<p>You are more than welcome to visit the club to find out more.</p>
					
					<p>The Club currently has fleets of Laser, GP14, Topper, Enterprise, 
					Albacore, National Twelve, RS Vareo, Merlin Rocket, Solo, Lark; and 
					welcomes other monohull dinghies without trapeze up to 14'6" in 
					length. Bowsprits may not be deployed during Club racing sessions.</p>
					
					<h2>SCHEDULE OF FEES</h2>

					<p>The Club year runs for 12 months from 1st October<br>
					The subscriptions below are for the Club Year commencing 1st October 2011<br>
					These fees will cover Membership until 30th September 2012</p>

					<h3>JOINING FEES</h3>

					<p>Entrance Fee Ordinary Members £25<br>
					Club Key Hire £7</p>

					<h2>ANNUAL FEES</h2>

					<h3>SUBSCRIPTIONS</h3>	

					<p>Ordinary Members	£96<br>	
					Associate Members	£16<br>
					Junior Members (<18)	£16<br>	
					Family Subscription Limit	£119<br>
					Intermediate Members (<21)	£25<br>
					Student Member	£25<br>
					Senior Members (60-69)	£72<br>
					Senior Members (70+)	£48<br>
					Social Members	£23<br>
					Temporary Members (per month)	£15</p>

					<h3>OTHER FEES</h3>
					<p>Boat Space in Dinghy Park	£18<br>
					Trailer kept in Dinghy Park	£5<br>
					B.W.B. Certificate	£10<br>
					RYA Affiliation	£4</p>
					
					<h3>Notes</h3>
					
					<p>Associate Members are the partners of Ordinary Members.<br>
					Junior Members are under 18 years of age at the beginning of the 
					January in the Membership year.<br>
					Intermediate Members are under 21 years of age at the beginning of
					 the January in the Membership year.<br>
					Senior Members are retired and are over 60 years of age at the 
					beginning of the January in the Membership year.<br>
					Family subscription covers children from 12 years of age at the 
					beginning of the January in the Membership year.<br>
					There is no membership for children under 12 years, but they can 
					of course sail if their parent is an Ordinary or Associate Member. </p>
